  "commentary": "With SPX at 6590.34 sitting just below the 6597 flip strike in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and will mechanically sell any push higher while buying dips, creating natural stabilization pressure. The massive +92M gamma wall at 6600 acts as a heavy resistance ceiling where dealer selling intensifies, while the detected wall break and GEX surge suggest recent volatility has dealers actively rehedging positions. Key levels to watch: 6597 flip strike as the regime pivot, 6600 as the primary resistance where dealer selling peaks, and 6560 downside support where negative gamma kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy range-bound trading between 6590-6600 with dealers capping upside moves.",
